## Payment Processing — CRITICAL RULES
```
Payment flows are the highest-risk multi-step operations.
EVERY payment implementation must follow:

Step 1: Create ORDER in DB (status: PENDING)
Step 2: Create payment intent with gateway (Razorpay/Stripe)
        → Store payment_intent_id in order record
        → If fails: order stays PENDING, user retries safely
Step 3: User completes payment on gateway
Step 4: Webhook received from gateway → verify signature (MANDATORY)
        → UPDATE order status: PAID
        → Trigger fulfillment
Step 5: If webhook fails/delayed → idempotent retry safe (check order status first)

NEVER:
- Trust client-side payment success confirmation (always verify webhook)
- Skip webhook signature verification (security vulnerability)
- Fulfill order without confirmed payment from gateway webhook
- Hard delete failed orders (mark FAILED, keep for reconciliation)
```

## WooCommerce Standards
- Custom plugins: proper hooks/filters, never modify core files
- Custom post types for products if default schema insufficient
- Payment gateways: extend WC_Payment_Gateway class
- Order status: use WC order status + custom statuses where needed
- Performance: object caching (Redis) for product/category queries
- Security: validate and sanitize all custom data (WordPress nonces)

## Shopify Standards
- Theme development: Liquid + Shopify CLI
- Apps: Shopify App (Node.js/Laravel) with proper OAuth
- Webhooks: verify HMAC signature on all incoming webhooks
- Metafields for custom product/order data
- Bulk operations API for large data imports/exports

## Custom Ecommerce (Laravel)
- Cart: Redis-backed session cart (not DB for guest users)
- Inventory: optimistic locking to prevent overselling
  (check and decrement in same transaction)
- Orders: state machine (PENDING → CONFIRMED → PROCESSING → SHIPPED → DELIVERED)
- Refunds: tracked as separate records, never modify original order
- Tax: calculate server-side, never trust client

## Performance for Product Catalog
- Product search: Meilisearch for instant search
- Category pages: Redis cache (15 min TTL, invalidate on product update)
- Product images: CDN + WebP format + lazy loading
- Filter queries: composite indexes on filterable attributes
